		<td><b>Re: Quite Possibly the Most Ambitious NES Port Ever (Concept</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />At first I found it weird that Arnold would be rendered with background tiles, isntead of the Predator, who's larger, but after thinking about it for a while, it actually makes sense: the Predator is controlled by the game, so it can be programmed to not share scanlines with other sprites (platforms and such), avoiding flicker, but Arnold, being controlled by the player, can go anywhere at any time.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


