	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It looks fine. It seems me and you had different opinions though: I went for more different colors and less gradients, and you went the other way around. I personally think that you overdid it a little though, as the gun is a brownish tinted gray and the armor is blue, which are a bit tricky to try and merge together. I'm also not to crazy about the orange in the skin. I know that it's the middle color between the brown and the pale, but I'd rather more contrast. Plus, it frees you a color for something else.<br /><br />Here's a comparison:<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<img src="./download/file.php?id=3133" alt="Sprites.png" /><br />
			<span class="gensmall">Sprites.png [ 4.62 KiB | Viewed 1426 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br />(One neat thing to mention is that the character's arm's are actually seperate sprites. Obviously, that wouldn't work on the NES...)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
